# Morning Brief

Deliver a scannable morning briefing. {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} reads it once and knows what the day looks like.

## Suppression + forward notes

Before flagging any item, consult the `note-management` directive store:
```bash
python3 {{WORKSPACE_ROOT}}/skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py check "<item text>" --scope morning-brief
```
Drop items where `surface: false`.

Pull today's forward notes ("for today" reminders {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} captured earlier):
```bash
python3 {{WORKSPACE_ROOT}}/skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py reminders --scope morning-brief
```
Incorporate them into the brief.

## Data (fetch in parallel)

**Calendar**
```bash
{{#GMAIL_ACCOUNTS}}gog -a {{.}} calendar list --today
{{/GMAIL_ACCOUNTS}}
```

**Open tasks** — Notion DB `{{NOTION_TASKS_DB_ID}}`, filter Status ≠ Done.

**Emails** — unread, last 24h:
```bash
{{#GMAIL_ACCOUNTS}}gog -a {{.}} gmail messages search 'is:unread newer_than:1d' --limit 30 --json
{{/GMAIL_ACCOUNTS}}
```

{{#IF_SLACK}}
**Slack** — last 8h in critical channels:
```bash
python3 {{WORKSPACE_ROOT}}/skills/morning-brief/scripts/slack_overnight.py --channels "{{SLACK_CRITICAL_CHANNELS}}"
```
{{/IF_SLACK}}

## Output

Print inline. Skip any empty section.

```
🌅 Good morning {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}}

📅 CALENDAR
• [time] — [event]

✅ TASKS
• [top-priority open task]

📧 EMAILS
• **Sender** — subject — action

{{#IF_SLACK}}🚨 SLACK
• **#channel** — summary
{{/IF_SLACK}}
```

